column5: Hi folks, I've been away fish'n for a few days and got home about noon today.  I posted last week about a severe storm that hit the Peterboro area and did some damage in our trailer park, so I thought I'd share a couple pictures of a cottage that was in the wrong place at the wrong time.  This tree was probably 30" wide across the trunk so the cottage didn't have a chance, but fortunately there was nobody around it, so there were no injuries. Another tree came down about 100 yards away and hit a trailer but didn't do any serious damage to it.  Scary stuff, but like I said, no injuries and buildings can easily be replaced.  Keep your head up when the winds start to howl
YIKES  Hope you had a good weekend anyway Lew.

That looks pretty much like a right off and total rebuild coming, could have been a tragic ending for someone.  Hope they had some insurance.  Kinda makes me glad my old trailer is a little further away from the big trees.

Hi Lew, That's a bit of damage, glad no one was in there.  That was a nice musky that you caught.  I fished for another 4hrs. not even a follow........ I'll be up there in couple of weeks give it another shot.
i really hope it was insured!  THat is terrible.
Dang thats one messed up cottage hope there insurance covers it if so they they will have a nice new one to make new memories in.
looks pretty bad, good thing no body was there.
mother natures wrath wow glad noboddy got hurt
That sucks!!! I am sure they had insurance!
That'll leave a mark!!! Mother Nature can sure reek some havoc when she wants to. Glad nobody was hurt.
at least no one was hurt or worse
WOW, Lew, that is some scary.  Thanks for sharing those pics.  Joey
Wow, that's quite the damage, glad no one was there.  Must have been pretty scary for those who were in the park at the time though.  Maureen
OUCH.....don't mess with mother nature.  Regards, Sam
I like trees Lew, but farther away from the house.
